WEBVTT

00:00:01.100 --> 00:00:09.580
Welcome to our program. This month's theme is, you are precious to Jehovah. Here

00:00:09.580 --> 00:00:14.939
are some highlights. When we're going through difficult times, does Jehovah

00:00:14.939 --> 00:00:21.739
notice? As we'll learn in Malu's experience, Jehovah does care and he helps us

00:00:21.739 --> 00:00:27.300
overcome even the most challenging circumstances. Prayer is a powerful way

00:00:27.300 --> 00:00:32.859
that we can ask for and receive loving comfort from Jehovah. We'll see that in

00:00:32.859 --> 00:00:38.060
our new music video. Soon all over the earth, Jehovah's witnesses will be

00:00:38.060 --> 00:00:42.820
inviting people to this year's conventions. Can attending a convention change a

00:00:42.820 --> 00:00:50.020
person's life? We'll find out in this report. Welcome to the April 2020

00:00:50.020 --> 00:01:15.000
edition of J.W. Broadcasting. We begin with the experience of Juan Pablo

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:27.060
Sermenio. Notice how he found a life of real meaning and purpose. When you're

00:01:27.060 --> 00:01:39.019
a little, you just want to be happy. But sadly, my father had a problem with

00:01:39.019 --> 00:01:54.799
alcohol and no child wants to live through that. One day, my family from the

00:01:54.799 --> 00:02:02.700
United States came to visit us. They look so happy. The way they talked it was

00:02:02.700 --> 00:02:12.120
as though they only had fun. A good life, no economic problems. I was shocked. I

00:02:12.120 --> 00:02:18.000
asked myself, how can we live in such poverty while their life is so great? That

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:35.819
was the life I wanted for my family. So when I was nine years old, I left my

00:02:35.819 --> 00:02:40.699
mother and the rest of my family to cross the border into the United States. I

00:02:42.629 --> 00:02:49.430
lived in a pretty rough neighborhood. So I joined a local gym to learn how to

00:02:49.430 --> 00:02:59.389
defend myself. The trainer Leo, he was like a father to me. He always tried to

00:02:59.389 --> 00:03:06.860
give us good advice. Raymond was part of the boxing team. He was a good friend.

00:03:06.860 --> 00:03:14.060
We got along really well. He respected me and he looked after me. After several

00:03:14.060 --> 00:03:18.139
years of being around Raymond and the other members of the team, I felt

00:03:18.139 --> 00:03:23.659
really comfortable. To some extent, I admired him because I could see he

00:03:23.659 --> 00:03:31.580
really doing well because Raymond was selling drugs. I knew that it wasn't right.

00:03:31.580 --> 00:03:39.819
By the time, I began to sell drugs as well. Raymond was in a drug deal gone

00:03:39.819 --> 00:03:51.219
wrong where he was murdered. I said to myself, this could happen to me too. It

00:03:51.219 --> 00:04:07.569
had been six years since I had seen my mom and my siblings. My mother was

00:04:07.569 --> 00:04:13.400
studying the Bible with Jehovah's Witnesses. It helped her cope with a lot of

00:04:13.400 --> 00:04:23.240
suffering. It brought her peace. She was so happy. I began to realize that this

00:04:23.240 --> 00:04:29.160
was what I really needed. I also thought about my friends at the gym. I wanted

00:04:29.160 --> 00:04:35.560
them to understand why life was so hard for all of us. So I returned to the

00:04:35.560 --> 00:04:43.680
United States. But they weren't interested. My trainer Leo told me I didn't need

00:04:43.680 --> 00:04:48.800
to sell drugs anymore. He could make me a professional boxer and I could help

00:04:48.800 --> 00:05:03.860
up my family in that way. He even gave me a nickname, the Bible boy. But I

00:05:03.860 --> 00:05:09.860
realized that was just a temporary solution. What I was learning was going to

00:05:09.860 --> 00:05:16.779
help forever. I was determined to serve Jehovah. I returned to Mexico. I started

00:05:16.779 --> 00:05:21.939
to study the Bible and take it seriously. I began to view Jehovah as my father

00:05:21.939 --> 00:05:27.860
because he helped me to find real relief from my pain. To have peace. A

00:05:27.860 --> 00:05:35.980
tranquility that makes you feel accepted, loved, and wanted. I have enjoyed an

00:05:35.980 --> 00:05:45.779
incredible life serving Jehovah. Decades later, my father was baptized as one of

00:05:45.779 --> 00:05:52.779
Jehovah's Witnesses. Jehovah has been so kind to me. My family and my siblings.

00:05:52.779 --> 00:06:00.019
Truly, I have no way to repay Jehovah for the life he has given me. I've had

00:06:00.019 --> 00:06:06.579
so many blessings in my life. A wonderful wife, great friends, including those

00:06:06.579 --> 00:06:13.939
that I serve alongside in Bethel. I'm not on my own anymore. Jehovah has given me

00:06:13.939 --> 00:06:23.139
a life full of real meaning, purpose, and so much happiness. Can you imagine

00:06:23.139 --> 00:06:29.060
leaving your home at the age of nine? One Pablo saw the better life, but that

00:06:29.060 --> 00:06:34.860
only led to danger and disappointment. One Pablo said it was Jehovah who gave

00:06:34.860 --> 00:06:41.540
him a life full of real meaning, purpose, and happiness. One Pablo is precious to

00:06:41.540 --> 00:06:48.779
Jehovah. As we mentioned, our theme for this month's program is, you are

00:06:48.779 --> 00:06:57.579
precious to Jehovah. How vital it is that we remind ourselves of that. Why? Well,

00:06:57.579 --> 00:07:03.420
let's consider three reasons. First, Satan wants us to believe that Jehovah

00:07:03.420 --> 00:07:10.500
doesn't love us or value our service. He wanted Job to believe that, but that was

00:07:10.500 --> 00:07:17.579
a lie in Job's day and it's still a lie today. A second reason that we need to

00:07:17.620 --> 00:07:22.660
be reminded that we're precious to Jehovah is because of negative circumstances or

00:07:22.660 --> 00:07:28.500
events that have taken place in our life. Severe illness, advancing years,

00:07:28.500 --> 00:07:35.500
injustices, mistreatment, a difficult family life, or other situations may

00:07:35.500 --> 00:07:41.699
call some brothers and sisters to feel that they're just not worth loving. Some may

00:07:41.699 --> 00:07:48.220
question why Jehovah allows those things to happen. Finally, we need reminders of

00:07:48.220 --> 00:07:53.060
how Jehovah feels about us because our imperfection can cause us to have

00:07:53.060 --> 00:07:58.259
negative thoughts. Some may still punish themselves for past mistakes,

00:07:58.259 --> 00:08:04.540
doubting that Jehovah has forgiven them or that he could ever love them. Others

00:08:04.540 --> 00:08:09.939
wage a constant battle against feelings of worthlessness. One witness wrote,

00:08:09.939 --> 00:08:16.699
Satan has done an excellent job of making even those who love Jehovah feel

00:08:16.699 --> 00:08:23.259
worthless and unlovable. I never felt worthy of Jehovah's love, so I tried to do

00:08:23.259 --> 00:08:28.379
more and more in his service as a way of earning that love. So no matter how

00:08:28.379 --> 00:08:33.179
many hours I spent in the ministry or how many people I helped, I felt it was

00:08:33.179 --> 00:08:42.539
not enough. I saw only the lack in me. One brother stated, I came from a family

00:08:42.539 --> 00:08:49.419
that showed little love. I was belittled, teased, and laughed at. So early in

00:08:49.419 --> 00:08:55.820
life, I felt worthless. I still carry entrenched feelings from my past that

00:08:55.820 --> 00:09:00.899
beat me down when I experienced calamity. When I stopped serving as a

00:09:00.899 --> 00:09:08.220
congregation elder, I felt like a failure as usual. To God, my family, and my

00:09:08.220 --> 00:09:14.690
brothers in the congregation. If you've experienced such feelings, you're not

00:09:14.690 --> 00:09:21.450
alone. So how can you be assured of Jehovah's interest? Let's examine three

00:09:21.450 --> 00:09:28.250
lines of evidence that prove your precious to Jehovah. First, we'll examine

00:09:28.250 --> 00:09:33.649
Jehovah's feelings for the nation of Israel. Second, we'll reflect on an event

00:09:33.649 --> 00:09:39.289
recorded in the Gospels. And third, we'll consider a modern-day example of one

00:09:39.289 --> 00:09:47.850
who was very precious to God. By the end of the 16th century BCE, millions of

00:09:47.850 --> 00:09:53.289
Israelites were enslaved in Egypt, where they were severely oppressed. In their

00:09:53.289 --> 00:10:00.210
distress, the Israelites cried out to Jehovah. How did he feel? Turn with me to

00:10:00.210 --> 00:10:06.009
Isaiah chapter 63, verse 9. The A-Portion reads,

00:10:06.009 --> 00:10:14.210
During all their distress, it was distressing to him. Did you notice? Not only did

00:10:14.210 --> 00:10:19.730
Jehovah see their troubles, he felt for his people, and he was moved to act in

00:10:19.730 --> 00:10:24.690
their behalf. Isaiah chapter 63 verse 9 goes on to say,

00:10:24.690 --> 00:10:32.570
In his love and compassion, he repurchased them. Jehovah couldn't see their

00:10:32.570 --> 00:10:37.690
suffering or hear their outcries without feeling for them, and doing something

00:10:37.690 --> 00:10:43.370
about it. That may remind us of the loving concern that a mother has for her

00:10:43.370 --> 00:10:49.370
newborn child. When that baby cries, the mother takes notice, and she feels for

00:10:49.370 --> 00:10:55.690
her child. In fact, notice how this is expressed at Isaiah chapter 49 verse 15.

00:10:55.690 --> 00:10:59.289
It reads,

00:10:59.289 --> 00:11:04.210
Can a woman forget her nursing child or have no compassion for the son of her

00:11:04.210 --> 00:11:13.049
womb? Even if these women forget, I would never forget you. It's hard to

00:11:13.049 --> 00:11:17.929
imagine a mother forgetting to nourish and care for her nursing child. That baby

00:11:17.929 --> 00:11:24.090
is helpless. Day and night it needs its mother's attention. Sad to say,

00:11:24.090 --> 00:11:30.090
however, we hear at times of such maternal neglect. But what did Jehovah say to

00:11:30.090 --> 00:11:38.570
reassure the Israelites? I would never forget you. Yes, the tender compassion

00:11:38.570 --> 00:11:43.409
that Jehovah felt for his servants was immeasurably stronger than one of the

00:11:43.409 --> 00:11:48.649
most tender and natural feelings we can imagine. The compassion a mother

00:11:48.649 --> 00:11:54.409
normally feels for her baby. Jehovah's feelings for the Israelites are

00:11:54.409 --> 00:11:59.090
summed up in another expression in the book of Isaiah. Please read with me Isaiah

00:11:59.090 --> 00:12:03.250
chapter 43 verse 4.

00:12:03.250 --> 00:12:12.450
For you became precious in my eyes. You were honored and I have loved you. Jehovah

00:12:12.450 --> 00:12:18.460
clearly expressed his feelings for his people. As one of Jehovah's servants,

00:12:18.460 --> 00:12:24.500
you can be sure that he also loves you most tenderly. No matter what trials

00:12:24.500 --> 00:12:29.980
you're facing now or have endured in the past, Jehovah sees you and he feels

00:12:29.980 --> 00:12:37.620
for you. When you hurt, he hurts. You are far too precious to Jehovah for him

00:12:37.620 --> 00:12:43.379
to forget you. He remembers your past efforts and he sees your continuing

00:12:43.379 --> 00:12:49.700
efforts to please him. Notice how Jehovah promises to sustain and comfort his

00:12:49.700 --> 00:12:58.139
people according to Isaiah chapter 66 verses 12 and 13. You will nurse and be

00:12:58.139 --> 00:13:04.379
carried on the hip and you will be bounced on the knees as a mother comforts

00:13:04.379 --> 00:13:12.500
her son so I will keep comforting you. What a heartwarming scene. Imagine a

00:13:12.500 --> 00:13:19.019
loving mother carrying a baby on her hip or bouncing him on her knees. In this

00:13:19.019 --> 00:13:24.899
way, Jehovah touchingly illustrates the intensity and tenderness of his love

00:13:24.899 --> 00:13:31.620
for you. Just as Jehovah loved his people Israel, he likewise feels that you are

00:13:31.620 --> 00:13:40.419
very precious and dear. Never doubt that. A second example of how Jehovah feels

00:13:40.419 --> 00:13:45.259
about his faithful servants can be found in the gospels. Let's read what

00:13:45.259 --> 00:13:49.700
happened on one occasion when Jesus was at the temple in Jerusalem at Luke

00:13:49.700 --> 00:13:57.220
chapter 21 verses 1 through 4. Now as he looked up, he saw the rich dropping

00:13:57.220 --> 00:14:03.500
their gifts into the treasury chests. Then he saw a needy widow drop in two

00:14:03.500 --> 00:14:11.659
small coins, a very little value. And he said, truly I say to you that this poor

00:14:11.659 --> 00:14:17.539
widow put in more than they all did. For all of these put in gifts out of their

00:14:17.539 --> 00:14:25.580
surplus, but she, out of her want, or as the footnote says, poverty, put in all

00:14:25.580 --> 00:14:31.740
the means of living she had. The study note for verse 2 in the New World

00:14:31.779 --> 00:14:36.899
Translation of the Holy Scriptures tells us that the Greek word for needy may

00:14:36.899 --> 00:14:42.259
describe a person who lacks the basic necessities of life or someone for whom

00:14:42.259 --> 00:14:47.419
life is a great struggle. In the Christian Greek Scriptures, it is used only

00:14:47.419 --> 00:14:54.220
here. Just think about the widow's circumstances. Not only had she experienced

00:14:54.220 --> 00:14:59.179
the grief of losing her husband, her provider, but she also lived in a

00:14:59.220 --> 00:15:03.740
religious climate dominated by leaders who, according to Luke chapter 20

00:15:03.740 --> 00:15:10.019
verse 47, would devour the houses of the widows rather than help such vulnerable

00:15:10.019 --> 00:15:16.659
ones. That widow was so poor that her contribution to the temple was what a

00:15:16.659 --> 00:15:24.980
labor might earn in just a few minutes. Life wasn't easy for her. In fact, Jesus

00:15:24.980 --> 00:15:31.460
said that she put in all the means of living she had. Our publications have

00:15:31.460 --> 00:15:38.299
stated that the coins the widow contributed were likely to lepta. With eight

00:15:38.299 --> 00:15:43.019
lepta, a person could buy two sparrows, which were among the cheapest birds

00:15:43.019 --> 00:15:50.539
used for food. So the widow had only half the amount needed to buy one sparrow,

00:15:50.820 --> 00:15:56.259
hardly enough for a single meal. Yet both the widow and her contribution were

00:15:56.259 --> 00:16:02.419
valuable to Jehovah. Jesus said that her contribution was greater than the

00:16:02.419 --> 00:16:08.220
contributions of the rich. When she put those two small coins in the treasury

00:16:08.220 --> 00:16:12.980
chest, they would be mixed with what the rich had put in. To imperfect human

00:16:12.980 --> 00:16:19.019
eyes, they might seem lost, buried. Yet this precious widow was the one Jesus

00:16:19.019 --> 00:16:24.220
singled out for praise. When the treasury workers came across the coins, they

00:16:24.220 --> 00:16:29.659
wouldn't have known how precious the coins and their donor were to Jehovah. But

00:16:29.659 --> 00:16:34.539
God's view was the one that really mattered, not what other people thought, or

00:16:34.539 --> 00:16:40.620
even how that dear widow viewed herself. Like that widow, you may find that

00:16:40.620 --> 00:16:46.139
circumstances limit what you can contribute to Jehovah. Age,

00:16:46.139 --> 00:16:51.539
infirmities, or other circumstances beyond your control may limit the amount of

00:16:51.539 --> 00:16:56.659
time you're able to spend in the ministry. You might feel that your efforts are

00:16:56.659 --> 00:17:03.740
like those two small coins, a very little value. Still, we learned from this

00:17:03.740 --> 00:17:09.619
account of the needy widow that Jehovah notices, and he treasures each act done

00:17:09.619 --> 00:17:16.400
for him, especially when we do it despite difficult circumstances. For a

00:17:16.400 --> 00:17:22.380
moment, think back on your worship of Jehovah during the past year. Some of you

00:17:22.380 --> 00:17:27.059
may feel that you accomplished little. Your imperfect heart might cause you to

00:17:27.059 --> 00:17:32.779
wonder whether Jehovah was pleased with your efforts. However, did one of the

00:17:32.779 --> 00:17:39.339
hours you spent require a special sacrifice on your part? If Jehovah took

00:17:39.339 --> 00:17:44.859
notice of the widow dropping in those two coins and valued her contribution,

00:17:44.859 --> 00:17:49.700
don't you think he also noticed and values what you did for him during that

00:17:49.700 --> 00:17:56.700
hour? Jehovah values every gift, no matter how small, that springs from a heart

00:17:56.700 --> 00:18:02.539
motivated by love. He remembers, and he'll reward even the smallest

00:18:02.539 --> 00:18:08.220
contribution given in support of his kingdom. That's proof of how Jehovah feels

00:18:08.220 --> 00:18:15.589
about you. Finally, let's consider a modern-day example of one who was very

00:18:15.589 --> 00:18:22.950
precious to Jehovah. It's the experience of Sister Aretti Pina. Sister Pina lived

00:18:22.950 --> 00:18:27.890
on the southern coast of Albania in the town of Vlor. She was baptized in

00:18:27.890 --> 00:18:34.430
1928 at the age of 18. There was a strong congregation in Vlor in the 1930s,

00:18:34.430 --> 00:18:39.630
and Sister Pina was a zealous evangelizer who climbed up and down rugged

00:18:39.630 --> 00:18:45.829
mountains, preaching with her Bible in hand. In time, a congregation no longer

00:18:45.829 --> 00:18:52.150
existed in Vlor, and Sister Pina lost contact with the brothers. Yet, she kept

00:18:52.150 --> 00:18:56.950
preaching faithfully on her own. Do you think her efforts went unnoticed by

00:18:56.950 --> 00:19:01.950
Jehovah? Well, years later, word reached the brothers that there was an old

00:19:01.950 --> 00:19:08.109
senile woman who was reportedly preaching in Vlor. People thought she was crazy

00:19:08.150 --> 00:19:14.710
for keeping faith in God during years of totalitarian rule. Yet Sister Pina, now

00:19:14.710 --> 00:19:20.630
in her 80s, was anything but senile. When the brothers arrived at her home,

00:19:20.630 --> 00:19:26.950
Sister Pina invited them in, but she seemed somewhat reserved. When they

00:19:26.950 --> 00:19:33.150
explained that they were her spiritual brothers, she had no reaction. After a

00:19:33.150 --> 00:19:38.470
few minutes, Sister Pina started firing questions at the brothers. Do you believe

00:19:38.470 --> 00:19:43.750
in the Trinity? What is God's name? Do you believe in hellfire? What happens when

00:19:43.750 --> 00:19:49.630
we die? What about the earth? How many go to heaven? The brothers answered each

00:19:49.630 --> 00:19:58.069
question. Do you preach? She then asked. Yes, said one brother. We preach, but she

00:19:58.069 --> 00:20:03.750
responded. How do you preach? We preach from house to house, replied the

00:20:03.750 --> 00:20:11.109
brother. Now, I know that you are my brothers, she exclaimed. Only Jehovah's

00:20:11.109 --> 00:20:16.990
people preach from house to house. Through her tears, Sister Pina stated,

00:20:16.990 --> 00:20:25.579
Jehovah is wonderful. He never forgot me. Sometime later, the brothers were

00:20:25.579 --> 00:20:29.619
notified that Sister Pina was ill and that she wanted to meet with one of the

00:20:29.619 --> 00:20:36.740
responsible brothers. When he arrived, she asked in part as she gasped for air,

00:20:36.740 --> 00:20:44.460
has the book of Revelation been fulfilled? The brother responded. Yes, Arati. Most

00:20:44.460 --> 00:20:52.259
of it has. Sister Pina said, now I can die in peace. I needed to know how close

00:20:52.259 --> 00:20:59.019
we are. Shortly after that conversation, Sister Pina faithfully finished her

00:20:59.019 --> 00:21:06.339
earthly course. What do you think? During all those years of isolation from the

00:21:06.339 --> 00:21:11.460
earthly part of Jehovah's organization, did Sister Pina's efforts go unnoticed by

00:21:11.460 --> 00:21:19.460
Jehovah? Absolutely not. Just imagine Jehovah's joy as he watched her faithfully

00:21:19.460 --> 00:21:25.339
doing what she could in his service. Do you think that Sister Pina was precious to

00:21:25.339 --> 00:21:32.980
Jehovah without a doubt she was? Well, your efforts in Jehovah's service do not

00:21:32.980 --> 00:21:41.670
go unnoticed by him either. Like Sister Pina, you are precious to him. So what is

00:21:41.670 --> 00:21:46.910
this consideration helped us to realize? We may have to contend with Satan's lies,

00:21:46.910 --> 00:21:53.470
negative circumstances, and events in our lives, and our own imperfections. But

00:21:53.509 --> 00:22:00.269
we should never forget that Jehovah highly values his servants. We saw that in his words

00:22:00.269 --> 00:22:06.630
to the Israelites through the prophet Isaiah. You can be sure that Jehovah loves you most

00:22:06.630 --> 00:22:13.230
tenderly. No matter what trials you're facing now or have endured in the past, Jehovah

00:22:13.230 --> 00:22:22.309
sees you and he feels for you. When you hurt, he hurts. Your far too precious to Jehovah

00:22:22.309 --> 00:22:29.420
for him to forget you. The account of the widow at Luke chapter 21 can assure you that

00:22:29.420 --> 00:22:35.299
all those circumstances may affect what you can contribute to Jehovah. He notices and

00:22:35.299 --> 00:22:43.059
treasures each act you do for him, especially when you do it in the face of difficult circumstances.

00:22:43.059 --> 00:22:51.140
He remembers and he will reward even the smallest contribution given in support of his kingdom.

00:22:51.140 --> 00:22:56.140
In what beautiful modern-day examples we have in the organization of brothers and sisters

00:22:56.140 --> 00:23:02.579
who have proven their loyalty to Jehovah and are precious to him. Like the example of Sister Pina.

00:23:02.579 --> 00:23:14.299
Dear brothers and sisters, please never forget that you are precious to Jehovah. Here's another

00:23:14.299 --> 00:23:22.500
modern-day example. Sister Malum Merck. As we'll see, she faced a number of serious hardships

00:23:22.500 --> 00:23:40.819
early in life. Notice all the ways she received comfort from Jehovah. My name is Malum Merck.

00:23:40.819 --> 00:23:55.119
No one can imagine how much Jehovah has helped me. I was raised in Sicimia in Greenland.

00:23:55.119 --> 00:24:03.039
My childhood was wonderful. We were very often out in nature. In the summer we sailed and in

00:24:03.039 --> 00:24:11.230
the winter we rode dogslets and we went hunting and fishing. When I was a child I was very close

00:24:11.230 --> 00:24:19.750
to my parents. I was a daddy's girl. He called me my beloved. So beloved became my nickname.

00:24:19.750 --> 00:24:25.269
It has been so wonderful to be raised in the truth. The greatest gift that I could get

00:24:25.269 --> 00:24:35.140
is to know Jehovah through them. When I was nine years old, my parents got divorced.

00:24:35.180 --> 00:24:42.220
It was terrible. I saw how my siblings were hurt. It cannot be explained how, I mean, we were

00:24:42.220 --> 00:24:48.579
very wounded in our hearts. When my parents divorced, my father was disfellowshipped. It was very

00:24:48.579 --> 00:24:57.579
hard to be separated like that. I missed my dad a lot. When my mom started to drink, I also

00:24:57.579 --> 00:25:03.900
felt abandoned. Because I knew what she had been doing. I was not surprised when after some

00:25:03.900 --> 00:25:15.500
time she was disfellowshipped. But of course I felt very hurt and sad. I supplicated Jehovah to help me

